    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90F/24</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-12">February 12,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Murray</hi>: I have noted that Mr. Kirk<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d665fn1">Alexander Kirk, Minister in Egypt and also accredited as
                        Minister to Saudi Arabia.</note> is due soon to leave for Saudi Arabia to
                    present his letters of credence.</p>
                <p>The President expressed to me two days ago his desire to establish a permanent
                    legation in Saudi Arabia, presumably at Jidda. It was his thought that Mr. Kirk
                    would remain as Minister accredited to both Saudi Arabia and to Egypt, but that
                    we would have a Chargé d’affaires with a small legation staff at Jidda
                    permanently on the spot.</p>
                <p>Please let me have your suggestions as to appropriate Foreign Service officers to
                    act in that capacity so that I may speak to Mr. Shaw.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d665fn2">G. Howland Shaw, Assistant Secretary of State.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
